2.   Consent to Electronic Disclosures and Notices; Paper Copies.
As part of your relationship with Spire, we want to ensure you have the information you need to effectively manage your Checking Pay access. We are required by law to give you certain information “in writing,” which means you are entitled to receive it on paper. We may, however, provide some of this information to you electronically, instead, with your prior consent. By accepting this Agreement, you agree and consent to receive electronically all communications, agreements, documents, notices and disclosures (collectively, “Electronic Communications”) that Spire and Chevron we provide in connection with Checking Pay. Electronic Communications include, but are not limited to: (a) agreements and policies you agree to (e.g., this User Terms and Conditions and the applicable Privacy Policies), including updates to these agreements or policies; (b) any periodic disclosures; (c) transaction summaries, confirmations or other information; (d) Checking Pay Access history; (e) customer service communications (such as claims of error communications); and (f) promotions, offers, or coupons. We may provide these Electronic Communications to you by emailing them to you at the primary email address listed in your Checking Pay Access, or by making them accessible in the Checking Pay app or applicable website. Communications will be provided online and viewable using in-app display features, browser software or .pdf files. In such cases, you will be able to print the Electronic Communication and/or have it emailed to you.
Electronic communications will be deemed received by you within 24 hours of the time such communication is posted or sent to you. You agree that if we send you an Electronic Communication but you do not receive it because your primary email address on file is incorrect, out of date, blocked by your service provider, or you are otherwise unable to receive Electronic Communications, we will be deemed to have provided the Electronic Communication to you. You may not be able to transact using Checking Pay until we receive a valid, working primary email address from you. You may print or save a copy of these Electronic Communications for your records as they may not be accessible online later.
You are responsible for maintaining all software and hardware necessary for receiving, viewing and maintaining record of the Electronic Communications. By your acceptance of this Agreement, you represent that you will maintain all hardware and software necessary to receive, view and maintain (including, but not limited to saving and/or printing) any Electronic Communications provided to you. You must have: (a) a valid email address on file with us; (b) a computer, mobile device, tablet or similar device with internet access and current browser software and computer software that is capable of receiving, accessing, displaying, and either printing or storing Electronic Communications received from us; (c) a current version an internet browser that Checking Pay supports; (d) an internet connection; and (e) sufficient storage space to save Electronic Communications (whether presented online, in emails or .pdf) or the ability to print Electronic Communications. We will notify you if there are any material changes to the hardware or software needed to receive Electronic Communications from us.
One copy of any Electronic Communication may be provided to you without charge by contacting Spire within 90 days of the original date of the communication. You may also request paper copies of any electronic communication within 90 days of the communication by contacting Spire at 888-823-2438 or CheckingPay@paywithspire.com, but we reserve the right to assess a reasonable fee for providing such paper copies after 90 days.
You may withdraw your consent to receive Electronic Communications by contacting us at 888-823-2438 or CheckingPay@paywithspire.com. If you fail to provide or if you withdraw your consent to receive Electronic Communications, Spire reserves the right to either deny your application for Checking Pay access, or restrict or close your Checking Pay access.
3. Description of the Service.
Upon completion of the Enrollment Application ("Application") and acceptance by Spire, you will become eligible to use Checking Pay, powered by Spire. Your Checking Pay access is not a bank account. Spire is not a bank, and does not offer banking or money service business ("MSB") services as those terms are defined by the United States Department of Treasury.  The Services allow merchants, from whom you buy goods or services, to directly debit your bank account as payment for goods and services.
4.   Enrollment Requirements.
To use Checking Pay or engage in any of the other Spire Services, you must enroll with us, in addition to any enrollment you may do with Chevron.  If you register as a Customer or otherwise use Checking Pay, you represent and warrant to Spire that: (i) you are 18 or older; (ii) you have provided a valid and functional email address which is owned and operated by you (pseudo, relay, or hidden email addresses may not be used); (iii) your enrollment and use of the Service is not prohibited by law; (iv) the account with your mobile service provider for the mobile device on which you are using Checking Pay is current and in good standing; (v) you will not use Checking Pay outside of the United States or Puerto Rico, for international transfers, or for any transaction requiring payment in foreign currency; and (vi) you have provided true, accurate, current and complete information about yourself as prompted by the Application (such information being the "Enrollment Data") and maintain and promptly update such information to keep it true, accurate, current and complete. For your convenience, some of this data may be pre-populated by Chevron, but you must review and correct it if/as applicable. If you provide any information that is untrue, inaccurate, not current or incomplete, or if Spire has reasonable grounds to suspect that such data is untrue, inaccurate, not current or incomplete, Spire has the right to suspend or terminate your enrollment, or your access to the Service and refuse any and all current or future use of the Service (or any portion thereof). By enrolling in and using the Service, in addition to the terms of this Agreement, you agree to comply with all applicable federal, state and local laws, rules and regulations. You will maintain the security of your access, take responsibility for all activities that occur using your access, and accept all risks of unauthorized access resulting from your acts or omissions.  You shall not share your phone, password, PIN or any of your credentials used for Spire Services nor use the Service through using the enrollment of any third party. You should not allow anyone else to access, use or borrow your Checking Pay access. Your enrollment, and this Agreement, is personal to you, and is not transferrable by you to any third party without the prior written consent of Spire.
You further represent that you will create and/or use only one checking account and are thereby entitled to the benefits of only one Checking Pay access when using the Spire Payment or Service(s). This checking account must be a consumer account and must be able to accept ACH debits and credits from your financial institution. Any creation of additional Checking Pay access device(s) shall be considered a violation of this Agreement. By registering for Spire, you hereby agree to all fees and penalties that may be applied to your Checking Pay usage in the event Spire deems your use of the Checking Pay as a violation of this Agreement, or in any way against the intended purpose or interest of the Services, as well as immediate termination of your Checking Pay Access(s). You understand and agree that Spire may choose to employ a collection agency or other business in an effort to collect any outstanding debts or fees associated with your usage, and you will not contest the use of a third party to collect the fees owed to Spire.
You agree that you will be responsible for any legal, court, or collection agency fees associated with rectifying your Checking Pay usage and all monies owed thereunder. You agree that Spire, or any agency or business employed by Spire, has the right to contact you via telephone, email or in-person using the information you provided upon enrollment or during any contact with Spire, in an effort to collect any monies and fees owed as a result of your access, whether specifically referenced in this Section or not, and such contact may be made in a manual or automated fashion.
