5.   Enrollee Authorizations.
When enrolling in Checking Pay, you are authorizing Spire, authorized vendors, and designees to verify your identity, verify your bank account, verify your equipment, and confirm you are the owner of the bank account that you would like to use. This may include asking you for further information and/or documentation about your account usage or identity, or requiring you to take steps to confirm ownership of your email address, mobile number, or financial accounts, and verifying your information against third party databases or through other sources. This process is for identity verification purposes.
There are two ways of verifying your bank information: Instant Account Verification which uses methods such as entering your banking credentials from participating banks or, alternatively, Spire can apply one or more challenge deposit/withdrawal transactions to a checking account you specify and subsequently ask you to verify those transaction amounts. Where applicable, when enrolling using one of the Instant Account Verification options:
(i) You authorize your wireless operator (AT&T, Sprint, T-Mobile, US Cellular, Verizon, or any other branded wireless operator) to disclose your mobile number, name, address, email, ACH or credit card information, network status, customer type, customer role, billing type, mobile device identifiers (IMSI and IMEI) and other subscriber status details, if available, to Spire to allow verification of your identity, to compare information you have provided to Spire with your wireless operator account profile information, and to autofill this form with your mobile operator account profile and payment information, for the duration of the business relationship.  You further authorize Spire to request your mobile carrier (AT&T, Sprint, T-Mobile, US Cellular, Verizon, or any other branded wireless carrier) to use your mobile subscriber details for verifying your identity and to autofill this form.  Those details may include name, billing address, email, phone number, mobile device identifiers (IMSI and IMEI) and other subscriber status details. Spire will store your information throughout the tenure of our business relationship.  See our
Privacy Policy
for how we treat your data.
(ii)   You also hereby grant Spire or its authorized vendor(s) a limited power of attorney, and you hereby appoint Spire and its authorized vendor(s) as your true and lawful attorney-in-fact and agent, with full power of substitution and re-substitution, for you and in your name, place and stead, in any and all capacities, to access third party internet sites, servers or documents, retrieve information, and use your information, all as described above, with the full power and authority to do and perform each and every act and thing requisite and necessary to be done in connection with such activities, as fully to all intents and purposes as you might or could do in person. YOU ACKNOWLEDGE AND AGREE THAT WHEN SPIRE OR ITS AUTHORIZED VENDOR(S) ACCESSES AND RETRIEVES INFORMATION FROM THIRD PARTY SITES, SPIRE AND/OR ITS AUTHORIZED VENDOR(S) ARE ACTING AS YOUR AGENT, AND NOT THE AGENT OR ON BEHALF OF Chevron OR ANY THE THIRD PARTY. You agree that third party account providers shall be entitled to rely on the foregoing authorization, agency and power of attorney granted by you.
(iii) You understand and agree that the methods by which Spire will verify you and your information through Instant Account Verification are not endorsed or sponsored by any third party account providers used in the process. You understand that if you have arranged for additional security controls, such as two-factor authentication with a third party account provider, the third party account provider may not require Spire to apply such security controls to use Checking Pay. You are licensing to Spire or its authorized vendor(s) any information, data, passwords, materials or other content (collectively, “Content”) you provide or that is obtained on your behalf through or to the verification process. Spire or its authorized vendor(s) may use, modify, display, distribute and create new material using such Content during the verification process or in providing Checking Pay. By submitting Content, you automatically agree, without any time limit, and without the payment of any fees, Spire or its authorized vendor(s) may use the Content during the verification and enrollment process, and use and store the information in order to provide Checking Pay to you.  As between Spire or its authorized vendor(s), Spire owns your confidential account information. You agree not to reverse engineer or reverse compile any of the service technology, including but not limited to, any Java applets associated with the verification or enrollment process.
Additionally, Spire may share data with third parties to verify your identity and authenticate information presented during enrollment. This may include sharing data to prevent actual or potential fraud or fraudulent activity. You are also expressly authorizing Spire or Spire's authorized vendor(s) the right, power and authority to (acting on your behalf) store, access and transmit your personal and financial information (such as from your bank) as reasonably necessary for Spire to provide Checking Pay to you. You also are authorizing Spire or Spire's authorized vendor(s) to access information from third parties to prevent fraud or fraudulent activity. See Spire’s
Privacy Policy
for how Spire treats your data.
By agreeing to this Agreement, you are authorizing Spire, its merchants, third party payment processors or other authorized vendors, and designees, to initiate Automated Clearing House (ACH) debit and credit entries to your account at the depository institution designated in the Application and to debit or credit such account on behalf of Chevron, for the verification of your checking account, or to collect any debts or fees owed under this Agreement. You can only use this service to pay for goods and services purchased at authorized merchants.
You understand that ACH transactions may take several days to post to your bank account. When you conduct this type of transaction, you are responsible for ensuring that the funds are available at the time the transaction is conducted and processed (posts) to your account.
You acknowledge that the origination of ACH transactions to your account must comply with the provisions of U.S. law. You also authorize Spire and its authorized vendors and designees to provide transaction history information to Chevron.
If you enroll in Checking Pay, you represent and warrant that you have authority to make withdrawals from and otherwise authorize debits and credits to the checking account designated in the Application. In the event that your bank does not allow electronic transactions, you authorize us or our authorized vendor(s) or designee(s) to convert the electronic transaction data to a paper draft for presentment to your bank. If any payment is returned for any reason (including NSF, Account Closed/Frozen, stop payment, account not found, etc.), you agree to pay Spire or its designee the amount of any ACH which is returned, plus the amount of the returned ACH fee and sales tax, as applicable per state law, along with any other applicable fees. Returned ACHs may be electronically re-presented to your bank for collection by Spire or its designee and will be debited by ACH from your account, without further notice, which procedures you authorize. You also agree to pay Spire or its designee a service charge for each ACH returned for any reason, equal to an amount up to the maximum fee under applicable state law or, if there is no maximum established by applicable state law, $35, which amount you agree is a reasonable minimum service charge. You also authorize the automatic debiting of such service charges and fees by ACH from your account. This fee is separate from any fees that your bank may impose for such returns.
We may share data with third parties to verify your identity and the validity of the data presented during enrollment.  By accepting this Agreement, you are authorizing us or our authorized vendor(s) to access information from third parties to verify your identity, to prevent fraud, and to authenticate information used to subscribe to Checking Pay in accordance with our Privacy Policy.
