(a) 	Through Checking Pay, Spire can be used as a method of payment for goods or services offered by Chevron locations, and/or for access to coupons, discount program(s), and/or or marketing communications. You must have enrolled with us to engage Checking Pay and/or available promotions. When you engage in Checking Pay or Promotions, you are bound by this Agreement and any other program-specific Terms.
(b)	Transaction types and limitations
i.
Access.
You may only use Checking Pay to pay for purchases at approved merchants.
ii.
Limitations on dollar amounts and frequency of Payments
— For security reasons, limits may be placed on the dollar amounts of individual transactions allowed on your Checking Pay account, the frequency of those transactions and/or on the cumulative dollar amounts of all transactions over a rolling day basis allowed on your Checking Pay account. These limitations may change from time to time in our sole discretion. The restrictions may exist even if you have funds in your checking account at the time you are attempting to use Checking Pay.
(c) 	Any coupon or discount program is specific to the issuer and/or merchant, and (unless otherwise noted therein) any corresponding Promotions (defined hereinafter) may not be used for goods and services from any other issuer and/or merchant. The issuer is solely responsible for all aspects of the coupons and/or discount program, honoring the coupons and/or discount program’s rewards and/or incentives (individually or collectively “Promotions”), any liabilities, injuries, losses or damages you may suffer in connection with the use of the coupons or discount program, and any unclaimed property liability arising from unredeemed Promotions, or any portion thereof. You acknowledge that Spire is not responsible for redeeming Promotions, or for any matter relating to the coupons or discount program or the Service in general.
(d) The Service is subject to the following conditions:
i. Any fraudulent use of Checking Pay or promotions in violation of this Agreement or any other applicable terms renders the payment void. The Spire Payment and Promotion are void to the extent prohibited by law.
ii. Unless expressly allowed by the merchant, Promotions cannot be combined with any other offers, certificates or promotions.
iii. Promotions may only be applied to goods or services sold by the merchant, and may not be applied to delivery, processing or handling fees. The Promotion may not be applied to gratuities, tax, or (unless expressly permitted by the merchant) gift cards, money orders or lottery tickets, or alcoholic beverages.
iv. iv.	Other than as provided below, the Promotion is only available only until the expiration date specified within the Service, or within the Promotion itself, or until issuer and/or merchant cancels the Promotion. However, some laws may require that Promotions have certain validity periods or require that Promotions not expire. If those laws apply, Spire will honor your legal entitlement to, as applicable, a credit for goods or services from the merchant beyond the expiration date. If such laws apply, you should contact Spire and request a credit or refund by emailing us at CheckingPay@paywithspire.com.
v. If the merchant permits use of Promotions for alcoholic beverages, some state laws may limit the redemption of Promotions for alcoholic beverages. The Promotions are valid only to the extent redemption is permitted by law. In addition, you acknowledge that Spire and merchants may offer some Promotions only to customers in certain age brackets, and you will not use any Promotion if you are not a member of the appropriate age bracket. The issuer and/or merchant is responsible for compliance with applicable laws with respect to the Spire Payment and issuance and redemption of the Promotion.
