13.   Our Liability for Failure to Complete Transactions.
If we delay or do not complete a transfer from your account in the correct amount according with our agreement with you, our liability shall be limited to your direct damages. However, there are some exceptions. To the extent allowed by law, we, Chevron and the merchants, will not be liable for indirect damages, consequential damages (including lost profits), extraordinary damages, special or punitive damages including, without limitation, lost profits or attorney’s fees, even if we are advised in advance of the possibility of such damages. We, and the merchants, will not be liable, for instance:
(a) If, through no fault of ours, you do not have enough money in your account to make the transfer;
(b) If a merchant refuses to accept your Checking Pay access;
(c) If an electronic terminal where you are making a transaction does not operate properly;
(d) If your Checking Pay access has been blocked, such as when you have unpaid transactions under this Agreement, transaction limitations are in place, or after you reported your phone, other access device or credentials are lost or stolen;
(e) If there is a hold or your access is restricted because of a legal process or other encumbrance restricting its use;
(f) If we have reason to believe the requested transaction is unauthorized;
(g) If circumstances beyond our control (such as fire, flood or computer or communication failure) prevent the completion of the transaction, despite reasonable precautions that we have taken.
Except for any other remedy described herein, your sole and exclusive remedy, and Spire’s and Chevron’ sole and exclusive liability, for any breach of this Agreement or for any other cause of action shall be (at Spire’s option) to remedy the failure or to give a credit to you of the amount owed.
