15.   Your Liability for Unauthorized Transfers and Misuse or Damage to Plastic Access Devices.
You must notify Spire immediately if you believe your phone or other access device has been lost or stolen, or if you believe your password, passcode, PIN, or any of your credentials used for Checking Pay has been lost, stolen or compromised. Telephoning is the best way of keeping your possible losses down.
Also, if your statement provided by the financial institution holding your account shows transfers made with your Checking Pay access or using your User ID or PIN/password that you did not make, tell us at once. If the state in which you established your Checking Pay access provides for limitations on liability for fraudulent use, such limitation shall apply in place of these provisions.
(a) Contact in event of unauthorized transfer: If you believe your phone, password, PIN or any of your credentials used for Checking Pay have been lost, stolen, or compromised call: 888-823-2438 or write: CheckingPay@paywithspire.com
(b) Business days: For purposes of these disclosures, our business days are (Monday through Friday). US holidays recognized by the Federal Reserve are not included.
Reimbursement, where applicable, shall be your sole and exclusive right and remedy for any Damages (as defined hereinafter) incurred by you arising out of, in connection with, or relating to any fraudulent use or suspected fraudulent use, and any payment of any fraud reimbursement amount will be conditioned on your signing an agreement in a form acceptable to us releasing us from any further claims with respect thereto. You agree not to knowingly flag false fraudulent claims, or knowingly report any false claims of fraudulent use. If you flag or report claims of fraudulent use that are inaccurate, deceptive or in any way fabricated, we reserve the right to cancel your Checking Pay access immediately, and seek Damages.
Where applicable, Spire shall not be held liable for any misuse, loss, theft, or damage of the plastic access device subsequent to the issuance to you. In the event of loss or theft of the plastic access device, you shall immediately notify Spire  to prevent unauthorized access and potential liability. Upon notification of loss or theft, Spire shall promptly deactivate the lost or stolen plastic access device and issue a replacement upon your request, subject to applicable fees and terms.
