Spire may change, modify or amend this Agreement by providing you notice of such change by Electronic Communication. Such changes will become effective 24 hours after being posted or sent to you. Your continued use of Checking Pay after the effective time of any such changes will constitute your acceptance of the changes. In the event you do not agree with any such changes, your sole and exclusive remedy is to terminate your use of Checking Pay by calling Customer Care and deactivating your Checking Pay access. Ceasing to use Checking Pay or removing the Checking Pay mobile app from your device will not terminate Checking Pay.  In order to terminate Checking Pay, your Checking Pay access must be closed.
Spire reserves the right to suspend your password and/or access to Checking Pay at any time if it believes you are in breach of this Agreement. If you use Checking Pay, you shall be bound by the version of the Agreement in effect at the time of your purchase. You are under an obligation to review the current version of this Agreement and other published Spire policies before using Checking Pay. We may ask you to affirmatively accept changes to these Terms at the time of your next login, access or use of Checking Pay. By continuing to use Checking Pay after such notice and/or acceptance, you agree to be bound by these Terms as modified.
Spire reserves the right to deny enrollment, suspend your password and/or access to Checking Pay, or terminate your Checking Pay access if Spire believes in its sole discretion that there are reasonable grounds for suspecting that you have: (a) acted in a manner inconsistent with the applicable local or federal laws, regulations or ordinances; (b) breached or violated any of Spire’s terms and conditions; (c) engaged in any fraudulent or dishonest behavior, theft, misconduct, or wrongdoing in connect with Checking Pay; (d) engaged in abusive, fraudulent, inappropriate, offensive or hostile conduct, whether it be physical or verbal in nature, towards Spire or any of its employees or contractors; (e) failed to pay any amounts that you owe Spire, whether in connection with your Checking Pay access or any other merchant branded access provided by Spire; (f) if information you have provided has been reported as, or is suspected to be, fraudulent or compromised; or (g) if you have not accessed Checking Pay in a period of time. If Spire believes, in its sole discretion, that your Checking Pay access been used for unauthorized, illegal or criminal proposes, whether by you or by some other party, you give Spire express authorization to: (a) share information related to use of your Checking Pay enrollment and access, including transaction information and your personal information; (b) take necessary steps to detect or respond to instances of potential or actual fraud or other illegal activities; (c) to respond to a law enforcement agency’s request for information or cooperation in an investigation; or (d) to respond to judicial process or other valid government investigation process.  In the event Spire denies enrollment because of an outstanding debt, Spire will provide you with a Fair Credit Reporting Act “adverse action” notice.
If your Checking Pay access is terminated for any reason or no reason, you agree: (a) to continue to be bound by this Agreement, (b) to immediately stop using Checking Pay, (c) that the license provided by Spire under this Agreement shall end, (d) that we reserve the right (but have no obligation) to delete all of the user data stored by Spire, (e) that Spire shall not be liable to you, or any third party, for compensation, reimbursement, or damages in connection with your use of Checking Pay or for termination of access to Checking Pay, and (f) you will remain liable for all payment transactions and other fees you initiated prior to the time of termination. Sections 3, 4, 5, 7-14 and 18, any accrued rights and remedies hereunder, and any other provisions that by their nature require survival in order to be effective, shall survive the termination or expiration of this Agreement.
